HEADWORD: Undertow
<hw>Un"der*tow`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The current that sets seaward near the bottom when waves are
breaking upon the shore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

